passmanExists

public static boolean passmanExists(java.lang.String key,
                                    boolean logIfMissing)
Check if value for key is stored in Passman

Parameters:
key - Key to check (format as for service "pub.security.outboundPasswords:getPassword")
logIfMissing - If set to true and no value is found in Passman, an error will logged
Returns:
true if value is stored in Passman, false otherwise

getAllPassmanEntriesFromServer

public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAllPassmanEntriesFromServer()
Retrieve all passman entries for WxConfig that are defined on the system by querying the server directly. Others services return them by looking at what is defined in config files.

Returns:
all passman entries that are defined on the system

getAllPassmanEntriesPkgDisabled

public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAllPassmanEntriesPkgDisabled()
Retrieve all passman entries that refer to a disabled package. For such entries it is not possible to determine whether they are orphaned or not, hence this separate list

Returns:
all passman entries belonging to a disabled package

getAllPassmanEntriesUnused

public static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAllPassmanEntriesUnused()
Retrieve all passman entries that are currently unused (excluding entries from disabled packages which are handled by getAllPassmanEntriesPkgDisabled()).

Returns:
all passman unused entries
